6:
You understand what I'm telling you,
right?
7:
Pharah... I'm counting on you to
remember what I told you.
12:
Hey! Nobody goes home until we
find that damn Cobra.
26:
Haha... My strength's really fading
now...
29:
This is bad... I'm going to starve to
death if I don't do something...
32:
You wouldn't be angry if I
pickpocketed a traveler or two,
would you?
38:
I can hardly believe that woman
managed to steal all of our money
in a mere moment I thought we
would have been used to
pickpockets by now...
47:
Heh... Why don't we try looking
around for her? I remember she had
short silver hair, for one thing.
52:
Sounds like a huge pain in the ass...
But I guess we don't have much
choice.
55:
Hey, you lot... You weren't bitten by
the Cobra, were you?
58: Cobra? What are you talking about?
61:
She's a famous thief-hunting thief. If
the woman you encountered was
alone and had silver hair, it was
probably her.
62:
I don't know much, but apparently
the thieves around here have been
rocked with infighting... I guess you
four got caught in the crossfire.
66: I see... Thank you for the information.
70:
A solo bandit hunter, eh? This is
going to be a real pain...
74:
Let us gather some information first
and determine whether this "Cobra"
is the culprit.
79:
Is this supposed to be the Cobra's
hideout? It doesn't look like anyone's
around...
83:
There's barely anything here. If she's
supposed to be some skilled thief,
you'd think there'd be more—
88:
...You're those travelers from earlier.
You've got a lot of nerve coming
here.
96:
...Wrong thief. I don't know who
might have told you that name...
99:
But you'd better not throw that
name around so casually...
Especially not with me around.
103:
Then please tell us your name. My
name is Stella.
107:
My blade is poisoned and ready for
blood... Do you have any idea what's
going on?
115:
...Hahaha. What's with those eyes?
Maybe you're tougher than you look.
118: Ha... Yeah, that's it for me.
124:
Our money? Huh? What the hell are
you doing?
137:
Don't get up yet. This is Starview
Village.
146:
Yeah, Stella told me to drag your ass
here. Maybe show a little gratitude?
151:
We'll ignore your previous actions
for now, but we need to ask you
what's going on.
155:
The thieves have been destroying
each other, and you got caught up
in the midst of it?
159:
It seems that you are famous for
being a thief-hunting-thief.
164:
Hahaha... I don't remember ever
claiming to be some sort of
antihero. I was just robbing people
to stay alive.
166:
But... A rumor spread that I was the
Cobra, and this is the result.
171:
Cobra. Would you like to live in
Starview Village?
179: No... I'm not... Don't call me that.
182:
Before you get the wrong idea, let
me tell you what I am: a
troublemaking bandit, and nothing
more.
184:
There's no point trying to help
someone like me.
189:
You're being hunted down by a lot of
people, aren't you? If you go back,
what exactly do you think you're
doing to do?
194:
...Surely, Starview would be a much
better place for you to stay in. At the
very least, nobody will be hunting
you here.
204:
...Are you insane? I don't get you
guys at all...
215:
Okay, Pharah. Welcome to Starview
Village.
219:
...Sorry for robbing you. Hate to be a
burden, but I'll stick around here for
a little while.
222:
I can at least lend you a hand for
the time being.
